article.description: — Bryson Mozone had 11 points and 14 rebounds to carry South Carolina Upstate to a 60-51 win over High Point on Thursday night, ending the Spartans’ season-opening nine-game losing streak.
article.headline: Mozone lifts SC-Upstate past High Point 60-51
article.linkText: Mozone lifts SC-Upstate past High Point 60-51
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- — Bryson Mozone had 11 points and 14 rebounds to carry South Carolina Upstate to a 60-51 win over High Point on Thursday night, ending the Spartans’ season-opening nine-game losing streak. Everette Hammond had 18 points and six rebounds for South Carolina Upstate (1-9, 1/3 Big South Conference). Tommy Bruner added 12 points. Bryson Childress had 17 points for the Panthers (3-6, 1-3). Lydell Elmore added 12 points and 13 rebounds. High Point beat the Spartans 63-51 on Wednesday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
